-- Omega Cuts Sunoco, Regal Entertainment, Buys Wellpoint, Apple
-- B y   W h i t n e y   K i s l i n g
-- 2012-05-14T19:28:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/omega-cuts-sunoco-regal-entertainment-buys-wellpoint-apple.html
Leon Cooperman’s Omega Advisors Inc.
reduced stakes in  Sunoco (SUN)  Inc. and  Regal Entertainment Group (RGC)  in
the first quarter while buying  Wellpoint Inc. (WLP)  and  Apple Inc. (AAPL)   Omega sold 1.4 million shares of Sunoco, the Philadelphia-
based refiner, during the three-month period that ended March
31, according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange
Commission today. The money manager bought 1.13 million shares
of Wellpoint, the No. 2 U.S. health plan, while exiting  EBay
Inc. (EBAY)  and opening a position in Sprint Nextel Corp.  Cooperman also sold 1.89 million shares of Regal
Entertainment. He bought 54,400 shares of Apple, the world’s
biggest company by market value.  Sunoco is up 28 percent since the end of the first quarter,
while Regal has gained 5.5 percent. Wellpoint fell 10 percent
and Apple dropped 6.5 percent.  Cooperman also exited positions in  Discovery Communications
Inc. (DISCA)  and  Cablevision Systems Corp. (CVC)   To contact the reporter on this story:
